<p><b>Oradour-sur-Glane</b> (<a href="/wiki/Occitan_language" title="Occitan language">Occitan</a>: <span lang="oc" xml:lang="oc"><i>Orador de Glana</i></span>) is a town and <a href="/wiki/Communes_of_France" title="Communes of France">commune</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Haute-Vienne" title="Haute-Vienne">Haute-Vienne</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Departments_of_France" title="Departments of France">département</a></i> of west-central <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a>.</p>
<p>The original village was destroyed on June 10, 1944, when 642 of its inhabitants were murdered by a German <a href="/wiki/Waffen-SS" title="Waffen-SS">Waffen-SS</a> company. A new village was built post-war on a nearby site and the original has been maintained as a memorial.</p>
